Conrad Martens was a prominent professional artist active from 1835 to 1878, renowned for his landscape paintings. His artistic style is characterized by a softening of the landscape, aligning with European sensibilities. Martens is particularly celebrated for his watercolor studies of Sydney Harbour, which are recognized for introducing Romantic ideals into his work.
